ngs\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b9a916b\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"91bda87\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"\\\"With...\\\"\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"748cd4a\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f4ff529\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3d082f7\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color: #242424; font-family: \'Crimson Text\'; font-size: 20px;\\\">A pet food bag claiming to be filled \\u201cwith chicken\\u201d or \\u201cwith real beef\\u201d is trickier than you\\u2019d assume. \\u201cWith\\u201d simply means that the aforementioned ingredients must not make up less than 3% of the product\\u2019s total weight. Many pet owners purchase bags made \\u201cwith\\u201d ingredients they recognize, not realizing that they are only technically required to make up 3% of the total package. The other 97%? Decidedly less familiar.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"7fdf2a1\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5bee80b\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"6a775e9\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"100% organic\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"59e65c0\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"fecf618\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7ea575b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Branding a product organic has become a proxy for actual nutrition information. A quick refresher: organic foods must be made without the use of antibiotics, artificial growth hormones, high fructose corn syrup, artificial dyes (which, btw, can be made from things like coal tar), artificial sweeteners derived from chemicals, synthetically created chemical pesticide and fertilizers, genetically engineered protein, sewage sludge, and irradiation.\\u00a0In other words, food deemed \\u201corganic\\u201d should really just be called \\u201cfood,\\u201d because neither you nor your pup should be eating any of the other stuff, anyway.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"9341db7\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5ab6031\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b5be7ef\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"But even organic cookies shouldn\\u2019t be eaten all day, every day in lieu of fresh food. (And for the record, all commercial kibble \\u2014 even the organic variety \\u2014 is so highly processed that much of the nutritional integrity of any individual ingredient is lost by the time it reaches your dog\\u2019s bowl.) Watch out for bags touting \\u201corganix\\u201d ingredients. Not entirely sure what \\u201corganix\\u201d means? We aren\\u2019t either.\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"67c593f\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2cd1f97\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"8613579\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Made \\u201cwith\\u201d organic ingredients\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"1ac55ac\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"c7f518f\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"cf387e2\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>This bold promise simply means that 70% of the ingredients in a product with this label are considered organic, while a product labeled \\u201call organic\\u201d guarantees that 95% of the total ingredients meet this criteria. But, again, organic doesn\\u2019t mean much when an ingredient has been burnt to a crisp and exposed to heat and moisture during extrusion, the process through which kibble is made.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"2ba4715\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"00aec38\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"003a905\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Feed-grade\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"6ec80ab\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"31924e5\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5580221\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Feed-grade is a far cry from food. Pet products with this label are not held to food safety standards and are considered unsuitable for human ingestion. Practically any ingredient is suitable for a feed-grade product, including waste, fats and grease, and dead animals from farms, ranches, and shelters. Some feed-grade pet products do use higher quality ingredients, but there is no method for consumers to differentiate between feed grade products.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"b25b931\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"fcb2224\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"57b6703\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Human-grade\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"9ec2ce8\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"55c6359\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"69cce74\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>This term simply means that a product in its entirety (not just individual ingredients) is safe for human consumption. A truly human grade pet food must be manufactured according to food safety standards and made with 100% food ingredients and human-grade supplements. This label has everything to do with safety and quality, and little to do with cook process. A wide array of pet foods \\u2014 including kibble, fresh, and dehydrated \\u2014 can all be human grade, with varying degrees of natural nutrients depending on how they are prepared. By regulation, raw pet foods are not allowed to claim that they are human grade.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"ac5c6ef\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f0cb0ec\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b42e35d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Natural\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f3635bb\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f8846e1\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2fd6b04\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>The USDA defines \\u201cnatural\\u201d as a product that has no artificial ingredients or added color, but doesn\\u2019t account for additives like antibiotics, growth hormones, or other chemicals. The term is so broad that the FDA is still struggling to come up with a legal definition for it. Legally speaking, there is no required difference between foods labeled \\u201call-natural\\u201d and \\u201cnatural.\\u201d Natural is not necessarily organic, but organic must be considered natural.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"4ce0f3a\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b84cbc8\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"bb022e9\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Gourmet\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"80b8a01\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3ccc9f7\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"0cc1196\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>We associate the term with fresh veggies and farm-to-table dining, but there are no legal regulations that determine when this term can be used on food labels.\\u00a0\\u00a0<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"c1bd583\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"095f914\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"a13166d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Grain-free\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"3f75980\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"fd940e3\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"47a2270\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>A product sans grain is technically free of corn, soy, wheat, barley, and oats. Grain-free products, however, are not necessarily low-carb; in reality, grain-free dog foods tend to have just as many carbohydrates as dog food that is not grain-free, especially when high-starch items, like potatoes, are used to replace grain.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"1a2a69b\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7d80980\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"947a01e\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Cage-free and\\/or free-range\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"e72bc14\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"014079f\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"e6f1800\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>\\u201cCage-free\\u201d is exactly what it sounds like: poultry that hasn\\u2019t been raised in a cage. But don\\u2019t be fooled \\u2014 cage-free isn\\u2019t as free or spacious as it sounds. Chickens raised for meat (even those that are \\u201ccage-free\\u201d) are typically kept in tight, indoor spaces that are cramped and uncomfortable. By USDA definition, \\u201ccage-free\\u201d and \\u201cfree-range\\u201d only require that animals have had access to the outside.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"9b183a7\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ce029c7\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7901705\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Grass-fed\",\"title_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":20,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"800\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"5c3d080\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"8b3ff1c\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"c29ffa2\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Though we might often associate \\u201cgrass-fed\\u201d with \\u201cfree-range,\\u201d one does not guarantee the other. Technically speaking, cows can be grass-fed and still contained, only let out to graze for short periods at a time. Though the USDA regulates how the term is used on labels, it does not regulate how, in practice, the \\u201cgrass-fed\\u201d animals are actually fed.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"8800c0e\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"6aca1db\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ba06a6b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>In the end, we recommend feeding only from the\\u00a0best dog food companies\\u00a0you know you can trust, and ideally choosing\\u00a0fresh food\\u00a0whenever possible. Stick to foods you can see and the whole feeding process becomes a lot less tricky.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Crimson Text\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":19,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.5,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_line_height_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"em\",\"size\":1.4,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_letter_spacing_tablet\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":-0.2,\"sizes\":[]},\"_margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"-10\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
