(2850, 1, '2019-09-25 10:25:48', '2019-09-25 08:25:48', 'In the days and weeks since Hurricanes Harvey and Irma, we’ve been blown away by the shelters and organizations working to rescue affected animals. Many shelters need&nbsp;supplies, while other organizations need additional resources as they transport dogs from high need areas.\n\nWant to help? Here are a few charities that currently need our support.\n\n<strong>Wings of Rescue\n</strong>Wings of Rescue is an all-volunteer organization that provides air transport for pets in overcrowded and dangerous high intake shelters. Since Hurricanes Harvey and Irma, they have&nbsp;flown 17 missions and saved over 1,500 dogs and cats from Texas, Florida, Louisiana, Puerto Rico, and St. Thomas.&nbsp;Donate&nbsp;to&nbsp;their emergency response team and help them continue saving pets.\n\n<strong>The Humane Society of the United States\n</strong>HSUS has been coordinating flights and ground transports from hurricane areas with their Emergency Placement Partners across the country. Their&nbsp;Animal Rescue Team is now deploying to Collier County, one of the areas hit by Hurricane Irma, and they are asking for help via their&nbsp;Disaster Relief Fund.', 'THE BEST WAYS TO HELP DOGS AFFECTED BY HURRICANES HARVEY & IRMA', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2215-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-25 10:25:48', '2019-09-25 08:25:48', '', 2215, 'http://foodog.test/2019/09/25/2215-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
